  3.696760539870386*^9},ExpressionUUID->"0aba7aa7-3a4e-4773-993b-\
85e81c22375f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"KineticExchangeSuperoperator", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<KineticExchangeSuperoperator[{i,j..},K,options] defines a kinetic \
exchange superoperator for dynamic exchange between the sites {i,j..}. The \
argument K may be be one of the following: (1) A square matrix of dimension \
equal to the number of exchanging sites, with elements given by the kinetic \
rate constants; (2) A list of the form {{i\[Rule]j,kji},{l\[Rule]m,kml}..} in \
which the rate constant kji for the conversion of site i into site j is \
specified explicitly, and similarly for the other rate constants. If the list \
contains an element of the form {i\[Rule]j,kji}, but no element for the \
opposite transformation {j\[Rule]i,kij}, the routine assumes kij=kji, i.e. \
symmetrical rate constants between sites i and j. Asymmetrical rate constants \
between i and j are defined by including elements of both forms \
{i\[Rule]j,kji} and {j\[Rule]i,kij}.\nIf the sites {i,j..} are omitted, the \
sites are taken from the current Sites[]. \\nThe options may include \
ImposeDetailedBalance\[Rule]True may be used to impose detailed balance \
automatically by adjustment of the diagonal elements. The default is \
ImposeDetailedBalance\[Rule]True.\nThe raw kinetic matrix may be extracted by \
applying KineticExchangeMatrix to the result.\>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.696759610347431*^9, 3.696759641360589*^9}, {
  3.696759678767851*^9, 3.6967597718626137`*^9}, {3.696759893403173*^9, 
